                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_106073">Great Fordham [Essex]</placeName>..
                         
                        <persName nymRef="Seburc">
                           <forename>Matilda</forename>, relict of <persName>
                              <forename>William</forename> 
                              <surname>Seburc</surname>
                           </persName> of <placeName role="person" key="place_106073">Fordham</placeName>
                        </persName>, grants to <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> de <surname>Ewell</surname>
                        </persName> of the same, for 40/-, a field with hedges and ditches, called <placeName type="minor">Haukeslond</placeName>, and a path, in the parish of <placeName key="place_106073">Great Fordham</placeName>. Rent: 2/-. 
                        Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Chaucie</surname>
                        </persName>,
                        <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Pol</surname>
                        </persName>, 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Bichedun</surname>
                        </persName>,
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Ralph</forename> 
                           <surname type="patronymic">son of Agnes</surname>
                        </persName>,
                        John his son, 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> 
                           <surname>Boli</surname>
                        </persName>,
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Stephen</forename> the <surname>cook</surname>
                        </persName>, 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname type="patronymic">son of William</surname>
                        </persName>,
                        John his son. 
                        Given at <placeName role="date" key="place_106073">Fordham</placeName>. 
                        <origDate when="1349-05-17">
                           <supplied>17 May 1349.</supplied>
                        </origDate> 
                        Endorsed, ’Carta de 4 acris terre vocatis Haukeslond ... quas Robertus Hoolde modo tenet in anno 8 Ric. II.’<note>Part of the same document as MS. Ch. Essex 193.<!-- check --></note> </p>
